org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulator.mutable.common

Class AbstractData<M extends DataManipulator<M,I>,I extends ImmutableDataManipulator<I,M>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulator.mutable.common.AbstractData<M,I>
  • Type Parameters:
    M - The mutable data manipulator type
    I - The immutable data manipulator type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataSerializable, DataManipulator<M,I>, ValueContainer<M>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractSingleData

    public abstract class AbstractData<M extends DataManipulator<M,I>,I extends ImmutableDataManipulator<I,M>>
extends Object
implements DataManipulator<M,I>
    A base abstract layer for implementing a DataManipulator. This provides all the otherwise "redundant" code dealing with various methods such as get(Key) or supports(Key) etc. The root of this implementation relies on a pseudo registration of registerFieldGetter(Key, Supplier), registerFieldSetter(Key, Consumer), and registerKeyValue(Key, Supplier) of which supply and consume values otherwise accessible by fields.

      • set

        public <E> M set(Key<? extends BaseValue<E>> key,
                 E value)
        Description copied from interface: DataManipulator
        Sets the supported Key's value such that the value is set on this DataManipulator without having to directly set the Value and DataManipulator.set(BaseValue) afterwards. The requirement for this to succeed is that the Key must be checked that it is supported via ValueContainer.supports(BaseValue) or ValueContainer.supports(Key) otherwise an IllegalArgumentException may be thrown. For fluency, after setting, this DataManipulator is returned.
